      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick), with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced red onion </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 3 min or until starting to soften</p>",
